---
title: Logistikos — Delivery execution sequence (accept → track → complete)
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor Driver
    actor Customer
    participant DFrontend as Driver Frontend
    participant CFrontend as Customer Frontend
    participant Controller as Rails Controller
    participant Acceptor as Orders::Acceptor
    participant Sidekiq as Sidekiq Workers
    participant PayAuth as PaymentAuthWorker
    participant Gateway as Payment Gateway
    participant GPS as useGpsTracking Hook
    participant LocWorker as LocationFlushWorker
    participant ETA as ETARecalcWorker
    participant DB as Supabase PostGIS
    participant Redis

    Driver->>DFrontend: Click "Accept order"
    DFrontend->>Controller: POST /assignments (Inertia)
    Controller->>Acceptor: Orders::Acceptor.call(order, driver)
    Acceptor->>DB: SELECT FOR UPDATE (optimistic lock)
    alt Order already taken
        DB-->>Acceptor: Lock conflict
        Acceptor-->>Controller: Error "Already taken"
        Controller-->>DFrontend: Flash error
    else Order available
        Acceptor->>DB: INSERT Assignment
        Acceptor->>DB: UPDATE order status → accepted
        Acceptor->>Sidekiq: Enqueue PaymentAuthWorker
        Acceptor->>Sidekiq: Enqueue NotificationWorker
        Acceptor->>Sidekiq: Enqueue FeedInvalidation
        Acceptor->>Sidekiq: Enqueue RouteSnapshotWorker
        Acceptor-->>Controller: Success
        Controller-->>DFrontend: Redirect → ActiveDelivery
    end

    Sidekiq->>PayAuth: Execute
    activate PayAuth
    PayAuth->>Gateway: authorize(amount, payment_method)
    Gateway-->>PayAuth: authorization_id
    PayAuth->>DB: UPDATE payment status → authorized
    deactivate PayAuth

    Note over Driver,Customer: Driver starts pickup

    Driver->>DFrontend: Tap "Start pickup"
    DFrontend->>Controller: PATCH /assignments/:id/status
    Controller->>DB: UPDATE status → pickup_in_progress
    DFrontend->>GPS: Start watchPosition()
    activate GPS

    loop Every 5-10 seconds
        GPS->>Redis: Buffer location update
        Redis->>LocWorker: Batch flush (10-15s)
        LocWorker->>DB: UPDATE assignment.driver_location
    end

    loop Every 30-60 seconds
        Sidekiq->>ETA: Recalculate
        ETA->>DB: pgr_dijkstra(current_pos → dropoff)
        DB-->>ETA: updated ETA
        ETA->>DB: UPDATE cached_eta_seconds
    end

    CFrontend->>Controller: GET /api/locations/:order_id (poll 5-15s)
    Controller->>DB: SELECT driver_location, cached_eta
    Controller-->>CFrontend: {lat, lng, eta, route_geojson}
    CFrontend->>Customer: Live map + ETA update

    Note over Driver,Customer: Driver completes delivery

    Driver->>DFrontend: Tap "Delivery complete"
    DFrontend->>Controller: PATCH /assignments/:id/status
    Controller->>DB: UPDATE status → completed
    GPS->>DFrontend: Stop watchPosition()
    deactivate GPS
    Controller->>Sidekiq: Enqueue PaymentCaptureWorker
    Sidekiq->>Gateway: capture(authorization_id)
    Gateway-->>Sidekiq: capture confirmed
    Sidekiq->>DB: UPDATE payment → captured
    Sidekiq->>DB: INSERT DriverEarning (net = gross - fee)
    Sidekiq->>DB: INSERT notification (customer)
